1
00:00:44,878 --> 00:00:47,965
THE LEGEND OF KITCHEN SOLDIER

2
00:00:48,715 --> 00:00:51,468
I must be crazy. I really must be.

3
00:00:51,969 --> 00:00:54,638
I still had leave left, but I just
had to come crawling back.

4
00:00:55,055 --> 00:00:56,098
Darn it.

5
00:00:56,682 --> 00:00:59,016
But still, it's good to have you
in the mess hall.

6
00:00:59,017 --> 00:01:00,852
It feels full and lively, sir.

7
00:01:02,145 --> 00:01:04,773
Right?
I do have a pretty big presence, don't I?

8
00:01:07,651 --> 00:01:09,819
You have advanced to Intermediate Cook.

9
00:01:09,820 --> 00:01:13,156
Your Basic Knife Skills speed
has increased by 1.5 times.

10
00:01:21,164 --> 00:01:23,709
Was he always that fast with a knife?

11
00:01:35,304 --> 00:01:37,013
Oh, Sergeant Yoon Dong-hyun.

12
00:01:37,014 --> 00:01:38,306
You can take a break.
I'll be done in a flash.

13
00:01:38,307 --> 00:01:39,391
All right. Wait, what?

14
00:01:40,392 --> 00:01:41,602
Aren't you pushing yourself too hard?

15
00:01:42,394 --> 00:01:43,812
This is nothing.

16
00:01:45,063 --> 00:01:48,399
Oh, right. Could you toss me
the sesame seeds?

17
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:49,401
Here!

18
00:01:49,568 --> 00:01:50,569
Yes, thank you.

19
00:01:56,867 --> 00:01:57,909
Impressive.

20
00:02:09,880 --> 00:02:15,052
Beef bulgogi, four stars.
Stir-fried anchovies, four stars.

21
00:02:16,470 --> 00:02:18,304
Level up.

22
00:02:18,305 --> 00:02:19,388
AVAILABLE SKILLS

23
00:02:19,389 --> 00:02:22,684
New Skill available. Check Gourmet Rating.

24
00:02:22,851 --> 00:02:24,853
Gourmet Rating? What's that?

25
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:29,524
Fulfill the Gourmet Rating
to earn additional rewards.

26
00:02:29,816 --> 00:02:31,860
So, are we ready for the guys to come in?

27
00:02:32,361 --> 00:02:34,862
GOURMET RATING

28
00:02:34,863 --> 00:02:36,448
This is so cool.

29
00:02:39,910 --> 00:02:40,952
GOURMET RATING

30
00:02:48,710 --> 00:02:52,129
What, you punk? Are you laughing
at your senior now?

31
00:02:52,130 --> 00:02:54,091
No, sir.

32
00:02:55,384 --> 00:02:58,637
Sergeant Yoon Dong-hyun,
what's your favorite dish?

33
00:02:58,804 --> 00:03:03,016
I don't eat for taste. I eat to see
how much protein I'm getting.

34
00:03:04,893 --> 00:03:08,145
Oh, protein is very important, sir.

35
00:03:08,146 --> 00:03:10,147
You don't sound very convinced.

36
00:03:10,148 --> 00:03:13,318
Hey, protein is essential
for building muscle, you know.

37
00:03:13,443 --> 00:03:14,778
All right. Salute.

38
00:03:16,029 --> 00:03:18,990
GOURMET RATING

39
00:03:20,534 --> 00:03:22,828
GOURMET RATING

40
00:03:25,163 --> 00:03:28,332
Kang Seong-jae, stop making the food
so delicious, all right?

41
00:03:28,333 --> 00:03:31,294
- I keep gaining weight because of you.
- Listen to you.

42
00:03:31,628 --> 00:03:34,297
You're talking like
Kang Seong-jae did all the cooking.

43
00:03:34,923 --> 00:03:38,301
You can tell Kang Seong-jae made this
just by how good it looks, sir.

44
00:03:41,346 --> 00:03:42,555
- You are acting up
- Enjoy your meal, sir.

45
00:03:42,556 --> 00:03:43,806
now that I'm powerless
before my discharge, right?

46
00:03:43,807 --> 00:03:44,932
- Enjoy your meal, sir.
- Thank you.

47
00:03:44,933 --> 00:03:46,934
- You don't even answer me.
- Enjoy your meal.

48
00:03:46,935 --> 00:03:48,644
- Enjoy your meal.
- Enjoy your meal.

49
00:03:48,645 --> 00:03:52,898
Today's menu is Korean Traditional
Style One, Two, Three, Four, and Five.

50
00:03:52,899 --> 00:03:58,572
GOURMET RATING

51
00:04:03,785 --> 00:04:06,912
GOURMET RATING

52
00:04:06,913 --> 00:04:09,039
You could've just said home-style Korean
meal. Why make it sound so complicated?

53
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:10,500
Home-style Korean meal.
Oh, so you understood?

54
00:04:10,876 --> 00:04:14,503
The very nature of a dish changes
depending on the name it's given.

55
00:04:14,504 --> 00:04:15,588
Yes, sure.

56
00:04:15,589 --> 00:04:17,882
What would someone who only eats
tofu and kimchi know about it?

57
00:04:17,883 --> 00:04:19,842
Jeez, you think I eat it
because I want to?

58
00:04:19,843 --> 00:04:22,012
I'd eat better stuff if we had it.
I eat it because there's nothing else.

59
00:04:27,601 --> 00:04:29,352
Private First Class Kang Seong-jae,
you got something to say?

60
00:04:30,353 --> 00:04:34,107
- No, sir. Enjoy your meal.
- How silly.

61
00:04:38,361 --> 00:04:39,404
What a jerk.

62
00:04:47,162 --> 00:04:52,292
GOURMET RATING

63
00:04:53,627 --> 00:04:56,045
GOURMET RATING

64
00:04:56,046 --> 00:04:58,756
What are you staring at? Where's my soup?

65
00:04:58,757 --> 00:05:02,719
Private First Class Tak Mun-ik,
I didn't realize you were so picky.

66
00:05:03,595 --> 00:05:05,012
Hey, TMI.

67
00:05:05,013 --> 00:05:06,931
Were you being sassy
and complaining about the food?

68
00:05:06,932 --> 00:05:09,391
Would a worthless Private First Class
like myself dare do such a thing, sir?

69
00:05:09,392 --> 00:05:10,977
I should just be grateful
for whatever I'm served.

70
00:05:11,353 --> 00:05:12,437
Right.

71
00:05:20,445 --> 00:05:23,198
The stir-fried anchovies are
well-cooked and not too sticky.

72
00:05:24,115 --> 00:05:27,911
The beef bulgogi isn't overdone,
so it's still tender and juicy.

73
00:06:02,404 --> 00:06:03,822
And the seasoning is perfect, sir.

74
00:06:14,457 --> 00:06:18,003
You have fulfilled the Gourmet Rating
for all the Ganglim Outpost Soldiers.

75
00:06:19,004 --> 00:06:21,130
You have earned bonus Experience Points.

76
00:06:21,131 --> 00:06:22,424
INTERMEDIATE COOK

77
00:06:26,011 --> 00:06:27,345
It's true that lately

78
00:06:28,138 --> 00:06:29,972
even when I complete a Quest,
my Experience Points

79
00:06:29,973 --> 00:06:31,433
don't increase like they used to.

80
00:06:32,726 --> 00:06:34,727
The higher the grade
of the dish you complete

81
00:06:34,728 --> 00:06:37,105
the more Experience Points
you can acquire.

82
00:06:37,647 --> 00:06:39,232
Higher grade?

83
00:06:39,858 --> 00:06:45,155
Oh, now that I think about it
I've never made a five-star dish before.

84
00:06:48,450 --> 00:06:50,702
EARN MORE EXPERIENCE POINTS
BY COMPLETING HIGHER-GRADE DISHES

85
00:06:54,789 --> 00:06:57,334
EPISODE 9

86
00:07:21,566 --> 00:07:24,778
Frozen yellow croaker.
Grade C from Jeju Island.

87
00:07:25,153 --> 00:07:26,404
Grade C?

88
00:07:30,116 --> 00:07:32,160
Can I make a five-star dish with this?

89
00:07:37,666 --> 00:07:40,877
Whatever, let's just do it.

90
00:07:55,767 --> 00:07:57,059
FRIED YELLOW CROAKER:
SPRINKLE A SMALL AMOUNT

91
00:07:57,060 --> 00:07:58,186
OF SALT, COOKING WINE, AND LEMON JUICE

92
00:08:09,781 --> 00:08:12,909
Hero, the oil is hot enough.

93
00:08:25,630 --> 00:08:27,090
What are you up to again?

94
00:08:32,345 --> 00:08:33,805
- Just finish it.
- Yes, sir.

95
00:08:42,105 --> 00:08:45,399
TERRIFYING MINESWEEPER

96
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:46,401
RESPECTED BATTALION COMMANDER

97
00:08:51,489 --> 00:08:55,367
- Salute! Yes, Battalion Commander.
- Seok-ho, have you had lunch?

98
00:08:55,368 --> 00:08:57,870
Yes, I have. Have you eaten,
Battalion Commander?

99
00:08:57,871 --> 00:08:59,664
I always make sure to eat well.

100
00:08:59,873 --> 00:09:01,623
From the sound of your voice,
Seok-ho, you sound

101
00:09:01,624 --> 00:09:04,001
completely out of energy,
as if you skipped lunch.

102
00:09:04,002 --> 00:09:05,295
Oh, that's not it.

103
00:09:06,087 --> 00:09:08,965
Come on, I can tell
just by the sound of your voice.

104
00:09:09,215 --> 00:09:11,926
It's plain as day that you're sulking
because Min-gu got promoted.

105
00:09:12,802 --> 00:09:15,304
Is that so? I'm really fine.

106
00:09:15,305 --> 00:09:18,265
Min-gu might have gotten
a bit of a head start

107
00:09:18,266 --> 00:09:21,227
but no one knows who will reach
the finish line first, you know?

108
00:09:21,895 --> 00:09:24,813
I'll make sure to back you up
during the next promotion review

109
00:09:24,814 --> 00:09:25,898
so don't worry.

110
00:09:25,899 --> 00:09:28,818
Battalion Commander, your words alone
are more than enough. Thank you.

111
00:09:30,361 --> 00:09:33,489
Anyway, to congratulate
the guys getting promoted

112
00:09:33,490 --> 00:09:35,949
the Regimental Commander wants everyone
to gather at the Officers' Mess.

113
00:09:35,950 --> 00:09:38,827
- The Company Commander has to be there.
- Well, if you're inviting me

114
00:09:38,828 --> 00:09:40,163
I'll definitely be there.

115
00:09:40,455 --> 00:09:43,290
The Ganglim men went through a lot
because of the typhoon.

116
00:09:43,291 --> 00:09:45,919
Bring the Outpost Commander and Private
First Class Kang Seong-jae with you.

117
00:09:47,837 --> 00:09:50,465
But why Private First Class
Kang Seong-jae?

118
00:09:51,216 --> 00:09:54,052
I just keep getting cravings
for his cooking.

119
00:09:54,385 --> 00:09:56,471
And it seems
the Regimental Commander is curious too.

120
00:09:58,723 --> 00:10:00,057
Battalion Commander.

121
00:10:00,058 --> 00:10:02,977
I, Hwang Seok-ho, will prepare
thoroughly and be there.

122
00:10:07,524 --> 00:10:08,775
Right.

123
00:10:10,193 --> 00:10:12,612
Hwang Seok-ho, let's get that promotion!

124
00:10:14,155 --> 00:10:15,740
MAINTAIN ORDER IN THE SERVING LINE

125
00:10:21,704 --> 00:10:23,747
Why are you doing all that
to a yellow croaker?

126
00:10:23,748 --> 00:10:25,707
You can just coat it in oil and fry it.

127
00:10:25,708 --> 00:10:27,960
Isn't that how you made the dish

128
00:10:27,961 --> 00:10:29,129
that we couldn't tell
if it was a croaker or a goby?

129
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:32,382
What is this?

130
00:10:33,842 --> 00:10:36,344
Just eat it. Next.

131
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:38,555
Private First Class Tak Mun-ik!

132
00:10:53,987 --> 00:10:56,948
FRIED YELLOW CROAKER

133
00:11:14,716 --> 00:11:15,967
If I do this...

134
00:11:19,012 --> 00:11:22,015
It will be the perfectly fried
yellow croaker.

135
00:11:30,565 --> 00:11:34,568
WELL-COOKED FRIED YELLOW CROAKER

136
00:11:34,569 --> 00:11:36,654
BUT NOT 5-STAR

137
00:11:37,739 --> 00:11:39,115
Well...

138
00:11:40,116 --> 00:11:41,534
This isn't it.

139
00:11:41,826 --> 00:11:44,037
Why? It looks delicious. I'll try it.

140
00:11:45,288 --> 00:11:48,833
WELL-COOKED FRIED YELLOW CROAKER
BUT NOT 5-STAR

141
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:58,133
This sauce is insane! It's delicious.

142
00:11:58,134 --> 00:12:00,011
What am I missing? My gosh.

143
00:12:03,097 --> 00:12:05,641
I'm not just saying that.
It's really delicious.

144
00:12:05,642 --> 00:12:07,393
So what are you so unhappy about?

145
00:12:07,602 --> 00:12:09,811
I don't know what the problem is.

146
00:12:09,812 --> 00:12:12,731
I mean, I need to know what the problem is

147
00:12:12,732 --> 00:12:15,776
so that I, Sergeant Yoon Dong-hyun
can decide whether or not to help you.

148
00:12:15,777 --> 00:12:17,862
There's this thing...

149
00:12:26,704 --> 00:12:29,415
- Geez.
- Hey. What's with the sigh?

150
00:12:29,874 --> 00:12:33,085
So, I guess someone like me
is no help to you now, right?

151
00:12:33,086 --> 00:12:34,336
You sucked up all my know-how

152
00:12:34,337 --> 00:12:36,004
during my final year of service,
and now you don't need me?

153
00:12:36,005 --> 00:12:37,464
Sergeant Yoon Dong-hyun.

154
00:12:37,465 --> 00:12:41,803
If the food I make is, say, four stars

155
00:12:42,470 --> 00:12:46,766
I feel like it's missing
that one thing to make it five.

156
00:12:47,767 --> 00:12:49,560
But I just don't know what that is.

157
00:12:51,896 --> 00:12:53,855
Now you're talking
like some kind of food critic?

158
00:12:53,856 --> 00:12:56,858
Hey, four stars, five stars...
That's just you being greedy.

159
00:12:56,859 --> 00:12:59,736
It's not like we have
a bunch of foodies around here.

160
00:12:59,737 --> 00:13:02,282
That kind of perfect food? That's for

161
00:13:02,615 --> 00:13:05,994
somewhere like the Officers' Mess.
They're not going to eat just anything.

162
00:13:07,912 --> 00:13:11,164
- You mean the Officers' Mess?
- Yes, the Officers' Mess.

163
00:13:11,165 --> 00:13:13,208
The Battalion Commander
specifically requested that I bring

164
00:13:13,209 --> 00:13:15,085
Private First Class Kang Seong-jae
to the Officers' Mess.

165
00:13:15,086 --> 00:13:18,630
The Officers' Mess is already full
of soldiers who are great cooks

166
00:13:18,631 --> 00:13:21,759
so why does he specifically want
to eat Seong-jae's food?

167
00:13:22,635 --> 00:13:25,846
Come on, how can a person
live on nothing but fine dining?

168
00:13:25,847 --> 00:13:27,556
I'm sure the Battalion Commander wants

169
00:13:27,557 --> 00:13:29,433
to hit up a snack bar
every once in a while, too.

170
00:13:29,434 --> 00:13:31,226
This is to celebrate
the Battalion Commander's promotion.

171
00:13:31,227 --> 00:13:34,396
And as a Company Commander, shouldn't I
at least grant him this one request?

172
00:13:34,397 --> 00:13:37,482
I'm just not sure it's appropriate for me
to attend such an important event.

173
00:13:37,483 --> 00:13:41,153
He specifically told me
to bring you along, Ye-rin.

174
00:13:41,154 --> 00:13:42,904
Our Battalion Commander...

175
00:13:42,905 --> 00:13:46,617
He can be a bit scary when he's serious
but he's a truly warm-hearted person.

176
00:13:50,246 --> 00:13:51,622
My goodness.

177
00:13:53,791 --> 00:13:57,002
Is our Private First Class
Kang Seong-jae already wondering

178
00:13:57,003 --> 00:13:58,254
what dishes he should make?

179
00:13:58,421 --> 00:14:02,215
- Well, it's just...
- Now, hold on.

180
00:14:02,216 --> 00:14:05,011
We can't actually serve
the Battalion Commander snack food.

181
00:14:05,595 --> 00:14:08,889
It should be something
a little luxurious, something.

182
00:14:08,890 --> 00:14:11,559
A menu that makes him feel like
he's being treated to something special.

183
00:14:12,143 --> 00:14:13,435
How should I put it? Something like...

184
00:14:13,436 --> 00:14:15,396
Like Korean royal cuisine.

185
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:17,523
Korean royal cuisine, all of a sudden?

186
00:14:17,815 --> 00:14:20,068
Why? How about sinseollo?

187
00:14:20,818 --> 00:14:23,653
Sinseollo, sir?

188
00:14:23,654 --> 00:14:26,531
Oh, does that have
perilla powder in it too?

189
00:14:26,532 --> 00:14:29,284
Company Commander,
don't you think overdoing it like that

190
00:14:29,285 --> 00:14:31,119
will just make things worse?

191
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:33,289
Okay. Private First Class Kang Seong-jae.

192
00:14:33,414 --> 00:14:35,083
Make sure to come up with a good idea.

193
00:14:35,792 --> 00:14:36,834
Got it?

194
00:14:41,005 --> 00:14:44,257
GANGLIM OUTPOST

195
00:14:44,258 --> 00:14:45,968
Private First Class Kang Seong-jae,
are you ready?

196
00:14:46,177 --> 00:14:50,472
- You mean right now, sir?
- Yes, come on, let's hurry.

197
00:14:50,473 --> 00:14:52,892
The Battalion Commander is waiting.
Now, let's get it!

198
00:14:57,605 --> 00:14:58,731
ROSE-KNIFE

199
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:01,024
Sergeant Yoon Dong-hyun, I'm heading out.

200
00:15:01,025 --> 00:15:02,026
Salute!

201
00:15:02,235 --> 00:15:03,277
Yes, Salute.

202
00:15:09,867 --> 00:15:12,703
Then who's going to make lunch
and do the dishes?

203
00:15:12,995 --> 00:15:15,498
My gosh. Don't go!

204
00:15:18,876 --> 00:15:20,002
Oh, right.

205
00:15:20,628 --> 00:15:21,711
Private First Class Kang Seong-jae.

206
00:15:21,712 --> 00:15:23,088
Private First Class Kang Seong-jae, sir.

207
00:15:23,089 --> 00:15:27,384
Are you ready to serve a perfect meal
to everyone in here?

208
00:15:27,385 --> 00:15:30,262
Since you believe in me
I'll do my absolute best.

209
00:15:30,263 --> 00:15:33,558
Let's show them
Ganglim is a force to be reckoned with.

210
00:15:37,979 --> 00:15:39,855
HOGUK HALL

211
00:15:39,856 --> 00:15:40,898
Hero.

212
00:15:41,858 --> 00:15:43,776
A new map has been unlocked.

213
00:15:45,611 --> 00:15:47,112
STAGE: OFFICERS' MESS

214
00:15:47,113 --> 00:15:48,197
The Officers' Mess.

215
00:15:49,073 --> 00:15:51,826
Welcome to the Officers' Mess.

216
00:15:52,994 --> 00:15:55,037
STRONG WILL, WE ARE ONE!
29TH DIVISION, 1ST BATTALION

217
00:15:56,831 --> 00:16:00,084
- Congratulations on your promotion.
- Congratulations!

218
00:16:02,378 --> 00:16:03,962
Salute!

219
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:06,131
Captain Hwang Seok-ho,
4th Company Commander.

220
00:16:06,132 --> 00:16:08,383
Seok-ho, Ye-rin, you're here.

221
00:16:08,384 --> 00:16:11,928
If the Battalion Commander calls for me
I'll be there, no matter where, sir.

222
00:16:11,929 --> 00:16:14,014
My sincerest congratulations
on your promotion.

223
00:16:14,015 --> 00:16:15,557
This is all thanks to you
for following my lead

224
00:16:15,558 --> 00:16:17,268
and helping me out, isn't it?

225
00:16:18,060 --> 00:16:20,729
Oh, the Regimental Commander said
he was curious

226
00:16:20,730 --> 00:16:22,147
so I brought Private First Class
Kang Seong-jae with me.

227
00:16:22,148 --> 00:16:23,231
Good.

228
00:16:23,232 --> 00:16:24,774
I hear the soldiers at Ganglim Outpost

229
00:16:24,775 --> 00:16:26,359
have been gaining a lot of weight
because of him.

230
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:28,320
That braised boneless pollock you made

231
00:16:28,321 --> 00:16:30,447
had a completely unexpected flavor.

232
00:16:30,448 --> 00:16:32,157
- Nice.
- Thank you.

233
00:16:32,158 --> 00:16:33,534
I knew you'd be like this.

234
00:16:33,868 --> 00:16:35,744
So, for the distinguished guests here

235
00:16:35,745 --> 00:16:36,995
Private First Class Kang Seong-jae

236
00:16:36,996 --> 00:16:38,664
will showcase his cooking.

237
00:16:40,041 --> 00:16:43,293
- Oh, really?
- Private First Class Kang Seong-jae.

238
00:16:43,294 --> 00:16:45,378
It's an honor to be invited
to such a special occasion.

239
00:16:45,379 --> 00:16:47,339
On the contrary,
having you congratulate me

240
00:16:47,340 --> 00:16:49,300
Private First Class Kang Seong-jae,
I'm so flattered.

241
00:16:53,387 --> 00:16:54,931
GOURMET RATING

242
00:16:56,057 --> 00:16:57,642
GOURMET RATING

243
00:17:00,228 --> 00:17:03,773
GOURMET RATING

244
00:17:10,780 --> 00:17:12,113
Five stars.

245
00:17:12,114 --> 00:17:14,991
Complete a five-star dish
for the Regimental Commander.

246
00:17:14,992 --> 00:17:16,243
Why?

247
00:17:16,244 --> 00:17:19,329
- Sir?
- Is there a fly on my head?

248
00:17:19,330 --> 00:17:20,705
No, that's not it, sir.

249
00:17:20,706 --> 00:17:22,457
It's just that I sense the powerful aura

250
00:17:22,458 --> 00:17:24,377
of a true gourmet from you,
Regimental Commander.

251
00:17:26,128 --> 00:17:29,464
Gosh, this kid is
a great judge of character.

252
00:17:29,465 --> 00:17:31,967
The Regimental Commander is
very particular about his food.

253
00:17:31,968 --> 00:17:36,346
I mean, he even keeps a whole list
of great restaurants on his phone.

254
00:17:36,347 --> 00:17:39,808
My wife is always nagging me
to eat whatever

255
00:17:39,809 --> 00:17:42,185
but if you're going to eat something,
it might as well be delicious, right?

256
00:17:42,186 --> 00:17:43,728
- Right.
- That's right.

257
00:17:43,729 --> 00:17:46,440
A man doing such important work
should only eat the best, shouldn't he?

258
00:17:47,650 --> 00:17:50,360
Private First Class Kang Seong-jae,
let's show him a delicious dish

259
00:17:50,361 --> 00:17:53,238
that's perfect
for the Regimental Commander's

260
00:17:53,239 --> 00:17:54,365
refined and noble palate.

261
00:17:55,533 --> 00:17:57,242
Yes, I'll get right on it.

262
00:17:57,243 --> 00:18:00,704
Hey, someone show this man to the kitchen.

263
00:18:00,705 --> 00:18:02,164
Yes, sir. I'll show him the way.

264
00:18:17,972 --> 00:18:20,724
- We don't have time. Let's move.
- Yes, sir.

265
00:18:20,725 --> 00:18:21,808
How can I help you?

266
00:18:21,809 --> 00:18:23,435
Salute!
Private First Class Kang Seong-jae.

267
00:18:23,436 --> 00:18:24,687
I'm here to assist in the kitchen.

268
00:18:25,062 --> 00:18:28,190
Oh, you don't have to salute.
We're informal here.

269
00:18:28,608 --> 00:18:29,816
Oh, okay.

270
00:18:29,817 --> 00:18:33,028
I was told to make a dish
to celebrate the promotion.

271
00:18:33,029 --> 00:18:35,615
But what should I do?
We weren't told anything about this.

272
00:18:36,532 --> 00:18:39,493
Let me check on that. Follow me.

273
00:18:45,291 --> 00:18:46,542
Corporal Lee Ho-yeong.

274
00:18:48,210 --> 00:18:49,919
This guy says he's from Ganglim Outpost

275
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:52,632
and that the Battalion Commander
ordered him to cook.

276
00:19:01,182 --> 00:19:04,517
We have more than enough people here.
Why bring in someone from Ganglim?

277
00:19:04,518 --> 00:19:05,561
That's what I'm saying.

278
00:19:06,687 --> 00:19:09,065
GOURMET RATING

279
00:19:10,816 --> 00:19:13,235
Gourmet Rating cannot be verified.

280
00:19:16,322 --> 00:19:18,198
Why are you staring at me like that?

281
00:19:18,199 --> 00:19:21,826
Private First Class Kang Seong-jae,
4th Company, Ganglim Outpost.

282
00:19:21,827 --> 00:19:22,952
I look forward to working with you.

283
00:19:22,953 --> 00:19:26,749
Outpost? I don't think a cook
from an outpost can do anything here.

284
00:19:27,166 --> 00:19:29,334
We already have a full course menu planned

285
00:19:29,335 --> 00:19:31,128
so I don't think we can just give you
something to do all of a sudden.

286
00:19:31,420 --> 00:19:35,799
Well, then...
I'll make a dish that I'm capable of.

287
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:37,468
And if you do?
When are you planning to serve it?

288
00:19:38,177 --> 00:19:41,137
- Pardon?
- The dining sequence is part of the meal

289
00:19:41,138 --> 00:19:43,224
and we can't have your dish
interrupting the flow.

290
00:19:45,309 --> 00:19:46,559
But still

291
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:48,353
if I make it delicious,
shouldn't that be enough?

292
00:19:48,354 --> 00:19:50,147
Oh, is that right?

293
00:19:50,815 --> 00:19:52,316
You can cook over there.

294
00:19:52,441 --> 00:19:55,402
As for ingredients, open the fridge
and grab whatever you need.

295
00:19:55,403 --> 00:19:56,487
Yes, I understand.

296
00:20:01,409 --> 00:20:03,034
Hey, who brought that guy in?

297
00:20:03,035 --> 00:20:04,495
They say he's from Ganglim Outpost.

298
00:20:05,454 --> 00:20:07,707
Gosh, he looks like a total dud.

299
00:20:07,873 --> 00:20:10,542
- This is going to be a pain.
- Is the prep done?

300
00:20:10,543 --> 00:20:12,877
- Not yet, sir.
- Then shut your traps and finish it.

301
00:20:12,878 --> 00:20:14,337
- Do we have enough time?
- No, sir.

302
00:20:14,338 --> 00:20:16,464
If you're done chaming the perilla
leaves, get the gastrique ready.

303
00:20:16,465 --> 00:20:19,885
- Yes, sir.
- Chaming? Prep...

304
00:20:20,553 --> 00:20:22,388
What's a gastrique?

305
00:20:23,848 --> 00:20:28,436
Prep, gastrique.
New keywords have been registered.

306
00:20:34,734 --> 00:20:36,735
I have to pull off a five-star dish

307
00:20:36,736 --> 00:20:38,320
that I've never even attempted before.

308
00:20:39,405 --> 00:20:42,825
First, I need to see what I can make
with the ingredients they have.

309
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:46,620
- Oh, I'm sorry.
- Darn it.

310
00:20:53,252 --> 00:20:54,295
My goodness.

311
00:21:17,777 --> 00:21:18,778
GRADE A ORGANIC CARROTS FROM JEJU ISLAND

312
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:20,863
Grade A organic carrots.

313
00:21:21,155 --> 00:21:22,906
Grown healthily in Jeju's volcanic soil

314
00:21:22,907 --> 00:21:24,825
without pesticides
or chemical fertilizers.

315
00:21:25,117 --> 00:21:28,078
Gosh, even the carrots they get here
are organic.

316
00:21:33,334 --> 00:21:36,836
Grade A Namhae spinach.
Grown in the clean sea breeze

317
00:21:36,837 --> 00:21:38,546
giving it thick leaves and a rich aroma.

318
00:21:38,547 --> 00:21:39,548
My goodness.

319
00:21:40,966 --> 00:21:43,092
Grade A Jeju black pork loin.

320
00:21:43,093 --> 00:21:46,305
Evenly marbled with fat,
making it tender, not tough.

321
00:21:50,184 --> 00:21:51,685
With ingredients like these...

322
00:21:55,147 --> 00:21:56,190
Okay.

323
00:22:09,245 --> 00:22:12,164
I can tell how fresh it is
just by the sound.

324
00:22:49,743 --> 00:22:50,744
Yes!

325
00:22:51,120 --> 00:22:52,913
Okay, I've got it.

326
00:22:55,833 --> 00:22:58,168
It's come back to this.
Braised boneless pollack.

327
00:22:58,794 --> 00:23:00,963
And without Kang Seong-jae,
this is a huge problem.

328
00:23:01,505 --> 00:23:02,965
Hey, there.

329
00:23:03,215 --> 00:23:05,592
What are you doing all alone
in your final year of service?

330
00:23:05,593 --> 00:23:07,760
Jeez, can't you tell?

331
00:23:07,761 --> 00:23:09,638
This is my punishment
for getting a bad junior.

332
00:23:09,847 --> 00:23:12,307
Gosh, that Kang Seong-jae is really
making things difficult for everyone.

333
00:23:12,308 --> 00:23:13,475
Look who's talking.

334
00:23:14,810 --> 00:23:16,687
- What are you doing in the kitchen?
- What do you think?

335
00:23:16,979 --> 00:23:18,730
The company administration officer said
not to leave you alone

336
00:23:18,731 --> 00:23:19,856
so he sent me to help out.

337
00:23:19,857 --> 00:23:22,734
No, I mean, there are
plenty of other guys, so why you?

338
00:23:22,735 --> 00:23:24,068
Well...

339
00:23:24,069 --> 00:23:27,156
Who else can put up
with Sergeant Yoon Dong-hyun?

340
00:23:27,448 --> 00:23:29,657
They've just stuck
the top two most senior guys

341
00:23:29,658 --> 00:23:32,786
at the outpost in the mess hall.
What a total mess.

342
00:23:33,829 --> 00:23:36,832
So, what should I start prepping?

343
00:23:38,375 --> 00:23:39,460
It's...

344
00:23:42,630 --> 00:23:43,839
Braised boneless pollack.

345
00:23:46,175 --> 00:23:47,176
What?

346
00:23:50,304 --> 00:23:52,222
Braised boneless pollack
without Kang Seong-jae?

347
00:23:54,266 --> 00:23:55,351
How are we supposed to make it?

348
00:23:59,563 --> 00:24:03,359
You have no idea how cute my daughter is.

349
00:24:04,401 --> 00:24:05,735
They say parents are a mirror
for their children

350
00:24:05,736 --> 00:24:08,364
and she copies everything I do.

351
00:24:11,825 --> 00:24:14,953
I've taken her out for so much good food

352
00:24:14,954 --> 00:24:17,331
that she's become quite the picky eater.

353
00:24:18,916 --> 00:24:21,376
My son just sits around
playing games all day.

354
00:24:21,377 --> 00:24:22,795
I have no idea who he takes after.

355
00:24:23,170 --> 00:24:25,380
It drives me crazy watching him.
Absolutely crazy.

356
00:24:25,381 --> 00:24:28,842
But nowadays, gaming is considered
a valuable skill, isn't it?

357
00:24:29,176 --> 00:24:31,052
The Republic of Korea is
a powerhouse in e-sports

358
00:24:31,053 --> 00:24:33,429
so you never know
he could become a great gamer.

359
00:24:33,430 --> 00:24:36,892
That's only if he's good at it.

360
00:24:37,184 --> 00:24:40,269
I don't know much about games,
but from what I've seen

361
00:24:40,270 --> 00:24:42,189
he's really terrible at it.

362
00:24:42,731 --> 00:24:45,650
If you don't have the talent for something
you should know when to quit.

363
00:24:45,651 --> 00:24:47,152
But he's stubborn about the wrong things.

364
00:24:50,280 --> 00:24:52,533
So, Outpost Commander,
what were you like as a kid?

365
00:24:53,325 --> 00:24:54,451
Well...

366
00:24:55,035 --> 00:24:58,580
I think I was just an ordinary student.

367
00:24:59,081 --> 00:25:01,583
You know, quiet and unremarkable.

368
00:25:02,668 --> 00:25:05,128
That's surprising.
I figured our Outpost Commander

369
00:25:05,129 --> 00:25:07,006
would've been quite something
back in school.

370
00:25:09,091 --> 00:25:10,591
The Company Commander would know, right?

371
00:25:10,592 --> 00:25:11,885
How stubborn our Outpost Commander is.

372
00:25:12,344 --> 00:25:13,554
Stubborn...

373
00:25:15,514 --> 00:25:17,766
She is, rather. Our Outpost Commander.

374
00:25:17,975 --> 00:25:20,644
Stubbornness. It's important.

375
00:25:21,562 --> 00:25:23,563
But telling the difference
between determination

376
00:25:23,564 --> 00:25:26,483
and just being pigheaded,
I think that's important too.

377
00:25:27,109 --> 00:25:29,737
Our people at Ganglim are all good.

378
00:25:30,029 --> 00:25:33,364
But I'm starting to see
these little shortcomings one by one.

379
00:25:33,365 --> 00:25:34,825
I'm only saying this
because it's a shame to see.

380
00:25:37,411 --> 00:25:38,454
Let's have a drink.

381
00:25:45,294 --> 00:25:46,586
Salute!

382
00:25:46,587 --> 00:25:49,757
This guy has a bit
of main character syndrome.

383
00:25:50,507 --> 00:25:52,050
I was a little late carrying out

384
00:25:52,051 --> 00:25:54,302
a grave mission befitting my new rank.

385
00:25:54,303 --> 00:25:55,678
And you got the job done?

386
00:25:55,679 --> 00:25:57,014
Yes, of course.

387
00:26:00,309 --> 00:26:01,393
Nice.

388
00:26:02,061 --> 00:26:04,354
I've been working all day
and haven't had a single decent meal.

389
00:26:05,147 --> 00:26:06,482
Thanks, 4th Company Commander.

390
00:26:07,775 --> 00:26:10,235
But you must not be very busy over there

391
00:26:10,611 --> 00:26:11,695
seeing as you got here so early.

392
00:26:41,600 --> 00:26:43,476
If you stir-fry it for too long

393
00:26:43,477 --> 00:26:45,562
the texture of the noodles will be ruined.

394
00:26:46,146 --> 00:26:49,316
The noodles might get soggy,
so be careful.

395
00:27:16,969 --> 00:27:19,137
Just mix the ingredients
and it's ready to go out.

396
00:27:19,138 --> 00:27:20,222
Just the ingredients.

397
00:27:29,731 --> 00:27:30,940
My goodness.

398
00:27:30,941 --> 00:27:32,817
When the Regimental Commander
dined with us before

399
00:27:32,818 --> 00:27:35,737
I heard him mention he eats lotus root
for his circulation

400
00:27:36,071 --> 00:27:37,864
so I prepared some fried lotus root chips.

401
00:27:37,865 --> 00:27:41,784
I fried thinly sliced lotus root,
and topped it with beef tartare.

402
00:27:41,785 --> 00:27:45,164
- Please enjoy. Salute!
- Thanks.

403
00:27:45,581 --> 00:27:48,374
I guess you have to be this good
to be a soldier in the Officers' Mess.

404
00:27:48,375 --> 00:27:51,336
This is why I can't help
but adore this guy.

405
00:27:51,795 --> 00:27:53,462
All right, then. At a time like this

406
00:27:53,463 --> 00:27:55,256
shouldn't we launch one of our missiles?

407
00:27:55,257 --> 00:27:58,135
Regimental Commander,
your timing is perfect as always.

408
00:28:02,014 --> 00:28:04,390
All right, missile.

409
00:28:04,391 --> 00:28:08,395
- For the future, for love, for work!
- Launch!

410
00:28:22,409 --> 00:28:24,995
The terrifying braised boneless pollack.

411
00:28:25,621 --> 00:28:27,915
Don't you think
we should at least do something?

412
00:28:28,582 --> 00:28:30,416
You saw what Kang Seong-jae
was doing, didn't you?

413
00:28:30,417 --> 00:28:32,627
I saw it. I only watched, though.

414
00:28:32,628 --> 00:28:34,212
Who knew a day like this would come again?

415
00:28:34,213 --> 00:28:35,464
And that I'd have to do it alone?

416
00:28:35,964 --> 00:28:39,217
Hey, that hurts. Really. You're not alone.

417
00:28:39,218 --> 00:28:40,551
While you were on leave

418
00:28:40,552 --> 00:28:42,345
I worked hard to get back to my old prime.

419
00:28:42,346 --> 00:28:43,388
So then...

420
00:28:43,889 --> 00:28:45,806
- Just the two of us?
- Yes.

421
00:28:45,807 --> 00:28:47,266
Shouldn't we show these kids

422
00:28:47,267 --> 00:28:48,936
we didn't eat
all that army food for nothing?

423
00:28:51,480 --> 00:28:54,273
Right. We may not be as good
as Kang Seong-jae

424
00:28:54,274 --> 00:28:55,483
but we can do this.

425
00:28:55,484 --> 00:28:56,985
- Yes!
- Let's do this!

426
00:29:07,829 --> 00:29:09,622
What? Wait a minute.

427
00:29:09,623 --> 00:29:10,874
- Why?
- What's wrong?

428
00:29:13,293 --> 00:29:14,461
What is going on here?

429
00:29:14,628 --> 00:29:16,712
Hey, where did Kang Seong-jae go?
And why is that guy here?

430
00:29:16,713 --> 00:29:19,674
What? Kang Seong-jae was called
to the Officers' Mess.

431
00:29:19,675 --> 00:29:23,262
- Darn it. This is driving me nuts.
- Hey, what's on the menu today?

432
00:29:26,390 --> 00:29:30,477
- Why?
- It's braised boneless pollack.

433
00:29:32,020 --> 00:29:35,314
I tasted it for seasoning,
and it's not bad, okay?

434
00:29:35,315 --> 00:29:36,857
So just take one bite

435
00:29:36,858 --> 00:29:40,779
and give me your honest, truthful opinion.

436
00:29:41,154 --> 00:29:42,613
The fact that Sergeant Yoon Dong-hyun
tasted it

437
00:29:42,614 --> 00:29:43,991
is what's really scary.

438
00:29:45,450 --> 00:29:48,036
Hey! I can't take it. Let's go.

439
00:29:52,291 --> 00:29:54,584
Where do you think you're going?

440
00:29:55,168 --> 00:29:57,169
This is the masterpiece
of Ganglim's top two cooks.

441
00:29:57,170 --> 00:29:58,630
Don't complain and go eat.

442
00:29:58,797 --> 00:30:01,507
I'll tell the company administration
officer that you're skipping your meal.

443
00:30:01,508 --> 00:30:02,967
Oh, dear.

444
00:30:02,968 --> 00:30:05,177
Do you really think this makes any sense?

445
00:30:05,178 --> 00:30:07,014
Sergeant Yoon Dong-hyun.

446
00:30:10,767 --> 00:30:11,768
Get in here.

447
00:30:22,362 --> 00:30:24,239
The last beef bone soup was edible

448
00:30:24,406 --> 00:30:25,823
so maybe the pollack will be good too?

449
00:30:25,824 --> 00:30:27,074
Corporal Joo Sang-uk.

450
00:30:27,075 --> 00:30:29,411
Do you know why people fall for scams?

451
00:30:29,911 --> 00:30:33,164
At first, they're really nice to you.
They make you trust them.

452
00:30:33,165 --> 00:30:35,249
Then the moment your suspicion fades

453
00:30:35,250 --> 00:30:37,336
they take everything you have
in one fell swoop.

454
00:30:38,754 --> 00:30:40,463
So you're saying
the beef bone soup was bait?

455
00:30:40,464 --> 00:30:41,590
Of course.

456
00:30:42,132 --> 00:30:44,717
Didn't I say I could do it too?

457
00:30:44,718 --> 00:30:46,635
The moment you think, "Looks okay,"

458
00:30:46,636 --> 00:30:48,804
and take a bite it's over.

459
00:30:48,805 --> 00:30:50,931
No one stick your spoons
in there carelessly.

460
00:30:50,932 --> 00:30:51,975
You'll be a goner.

461
00:30:56,521 --> 00:30:59,232
- Eat.
- Darn it.

462
00:31:00,692 --> 00:31:01,902
Whatever.

463
00:31:07,741 --> 00:31:10,035
What? Oh!

464
00:31:11,161 --> 00:31:13,496
I feel like they were really
going for it with this one.

465
00:31:13,497 --> 00:31:15,290
Hey, I'm telling you,
you're being scammed.

466
00:31:21,213 --> 00:31:22,296
What?

467
00:31:22,297 --> 00:31:23,757
What's going on
right before he's discharged?

468
00:31:28,762 --> 00:31:29,763
What?

469
00:31:30,764 --> 00:31:33,349
Isn't it a bad sign when a person changes
all of a sudden?

470
00:31:33,350 --> 00:31:34,476
This is delicious.

471
00:31:37,396 --> 00:31:38,522
It's delicious!

472
00:31:44,611 --> 00:31:46,654
- Darn it.
- Hey! Get it away!

473
00:31:46,655 --> 00:31:48,281
We really don't get along.

474
00:31:51,326 --> 00:31:55,956
KANG SEONG-JAE'S RECIPE NOTE

475
00:32:41,168 --> 00:32:45,254
JAPCHAE

476
00:32:45,255 --> 00:32:47,424
Japchae. Four stars.

477
00:32:47,591 --> 00:32:49,550
I followed the recipe perfectly.

478
00:32:49,551 --> 00:32:51,093
Let's get ready to serve the main dish!

479
00:32:51,094 --> 00:32:52,220
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

480
00:32:53,138 --> 00:32:54,763
If it's not a five-star dish

481
00:32:54,764 --> 00:32:56,766
it won't satisfy Regimental Commander.

482
00:32:57,434 --> 00:33:00,061
How can I get that final star?

483
00:33:00,937 --> 00:33:04,524
At this rate,
the quest will be a complete failure.

484
00:33:11,907 --> 00:33:13,033
Hey.

485
00:33:13,241 --> 00:33:16,536
- Are you taking that out now?
- Yes. I'm about to.

486
00:33:17,037 --> 00:33:18,454
- Let's take this out too.
- Yes.

487
00:33:18,455 --> 00:33:19,831
Wait, hold on a second.

488
00:33:19,956 --> 00:33:21,958
Why? Is there something else
you need to do?

489
00:33:23,627 --> 00:33:24,669
Well...

490
00:33:25,545 --> 00:33:28,673
It's just it feels like
it's missing a little something.

491
00:33:30,800 --> 00:33:31,885
Let me taste it.

492
00:33:44,940 --> 00:33:46,316
It seems fine.

493
00:33:51,112 --> 00:33:52,280
Should we serve it like this?

494
00:33:58,537 --> 00:34:01,373
No. It's not good enough yet.

495
00:34:18,181 --> 00:34:19,682
The dish we've prepared for you today

496
00:34:19,683 --> 00:34:22,977
is duck leg, marinated for 24 hours
in salt and various herbs.

497
00:34:22,978 --> 00:34:24,395
It was slow-cooked
for three and a half hours

498
00:34:24,396 --> 00:34:26,188
in 65°C duck fat
to create this duck confit

499
00:34:26,189 --> 00:34:28,941
which we've paired with
an orange gastrique sauce.

500
00:34:28,942 --> 00:34:30,693
Please enjoy the texture
of the crispy duck skin

501
00:34:30,694 --> 00:34:33,654
along with the tender meat.

502
00:34:33,655 --> 00:34:36,700
Gosh, is this really the same
duck dish we're used to?

503
00:34:37,993 --> 00:34:39,076
On such a special day

504
00:34:39,077 --> 00:34:42,121
we felt an ordinary dish wouldn't
properly convey our congratulations

505
00:34:42,122 --> 00:34:43,622
so we put a great deal of care into it.

506
00:34:43,623 --> 00:34:44,666
Please, enjoy your meal.

507
00:34:45,125 --> 00:34:46,167
Thanks!

508
00:34:50,630 --> 00:34:55,218
Gosh, just the smell of this
makes me feel full already.

509
00:34:56,386 --> 00:34:58,096
Please eat, Regimental Commander.

510
00:34:59,055 --> 00:35:01,683
- Oh, yes. Let's dig in.
- Yes, sir.

511
00:35:10,066 --> 00:35:11,900
JAPCHAE: SQUEEZE WATER FROM SPINACH,
ADD SALT AND SESAME OIL AND TOSS

512
00:35:11,901 --> 00:35:13,486
SOAK GLASS NOODLES IN WATER,
CUT THE ONION INTO BITE-SIZED PIECES

513
00:35:17,490 --> 00:35:18,617
Darn it.

514
00:35:19,117 --> 00:35:22,621
I feel like I need to find the solution
before I can start over.

515
00:35:22,829 --> 00:35:24,789
- Let's serve dessert.
- Yes.

516
00:35:34,841 --> 00:35:37,093
This feels more like a wake than a feast.

517
00:35:42,098 --> 00:35:44,559
- May I ask you something?
- Yes, what is it?

518
00:35:44,768 --> 00:35:47,395
When you make a dish
that isn't satisfactory

519
00:35:47,854 --> 00:35:49,856
how do you find a way forward?

520
00:35:50,607 --> 00:35:53,693
Until I can serve a dish that makes them
pick up their utensils again

521
00:35:54,277 --> 00:35:55,528
I'd just keep cooking.

522
00:35:55,695 --> 00:35:56,696
On and on.

523
00:35:57,614 --> 00:36:00,116
This dish is how they're going
to remember you, right?

524
00:36:19,844 --> 00:36:22,639
- Darn it, what is he doing?
- Just leave him be.

525
00:36:23,181 --> 00:36:26,142
- Let's see what he's got.
- Yes, understood.

526
00:36:36,444 --> 00:36:38,947
Japchae. Four stars.

527
00:36:45,537 --> 00:36:49,165
Add a special ingredient
to upgrade the dish's class.

528
00:37:21,489 --> 00:37:23,574
WILD PINE MUSHROOMS, GRADE S
FROM ULJIN, GYEONGBUK

529
00:37:23,575 --> 00:37:26,995
Wild pine mushrooms. Grade S.

530
00:37:30,248 --> 00:37:33,334
So Grade S ingredients really do exist.

531
00:37:34,127 --> 00:37:35,210
Its aroma is so intense

532
00:37:35,211 --> 00:37:38,256
it fills your mouth with flavor
even without any special preparation.

533
00:37:44,012 --> 00:37:46,264
Who would take a knife
to wild pine mushrooms?

534
00:37:47,015 --> 00:37:48,850
You have to tear it along the grain
to keep the aroma intact.

535
00:37:50,185 --> 00:37:51,269
Oh, I see.

536
00:37:53,229 --> 00:37:54,773
I didn't know that. Thank you.

537
00:38:16,711 --> 00:38:21,215
WILD PINE MUSHROOM JAPCHAE

538
00:38:21,216 --> 00:38:23,176
Wild pine mushroom japchae.

539
00:38:23,635 --> 00:38:27,763
By adding a Grade S ingredient,
one star is added.

540
00:38:27,764 --> 00:38:29,808
GUILTY OF BEING TOO DELICIOUS

541
00:38:30,099 --> 00:38:33,019
All right. Thanks to Corporal Lee Ho-yeong

542
00:38:33,478 --> 00:38:38,358
from the appetizer to the dessert,
we've enjoyed a full-course meal.

543
00:38:39,067 --> 00:38:40,567
We should have promotions more often.

544
00:38:40,568 --> 00:38:42,654
So we can eat lavish dishes like this.

545
00:38:43,822 --> 00:38:45,489
If I had my way

546
00:38:45,490 --> 00:38:48,576
I almost wish Corporal Lee Ho-yeong's
discharge date would never come.

547
00:38:48,952 --> 00:38:51,203
If you were to eat delicious food
like this on the outside

548
00:38:51,204 --> 00:38:53,665
- how much would you have to pay?
- That's right.

549
00:38:55,500 --> 00:38:56,584
What?

550
00:38:58,586 --> 00:39:01,672
- I'm sorry I'm late.
- Come to think of it

551
00:39:01,673 --> 00:39:04,467
Private First Class Kang Seong-jae's dish
is finally being served.

552
00:39:04,759 --> 00:39:07,469
Isn't this japchae?

553
00:39:07,470 --> 00:39:10,265
Yes. It's japchae
made with wild pine mushrooms.

554
00:39:11,099 --> 00:39:12,432
Can't you see

555
00:39:12,433 --> 00:39:14,101
that we've already finished our meal,
dessert and all?

556
00:39:14,102 --> 00:39:17,272
No, let's at least hear his reason
for making it.

557
00:39:18,022 --> 00:39:21,234
Of all the possible dishes,
why did you choose japchae?

558
00:39:23,862 --> 00:39:25,112
I chose it because

559
00:39:25,113 --> 00:39:27,115
it's an essential dish
for a feast like this one.

560
00:39:27,949 --> 00:39:31,703
Well, you're not wrong,
but since it's japchae

561
00:39:32,412 --> 00:39:34,288
I have to admit
I'm not really looking forward to it.

562
00:39:34,289 --> 00:39:37,375
We should have discussed the menu.
I'm sorry, sir.

563
00:39:44,090 --> 00:39:48,720
Gosh, but the aroma of the pine mushrooms
is quite wonderful.

564
00:40:05,695 --> 00:40:06,904
Order in the court.

565
00:40:06,905 --> 00:40:09,656
Your Honor, the defendant
armed itself with its aroma

566
00:40:09,657 --> 00:40:11,534
and bewitched the people.

567
00:40:13,036 --> 00:40:14,245
Objection.

568
00:40:14,412 --> 00:40:18,290
The defendant couldn't help
its own inherent aroma.

569
00:40:18,291 --> 00:40:20,710
Overruled. Continue, prosecutor.

570
00:40:23,046 --> 00:40:25,589
Furthermore, by simultaneously expressing

571
00:40:25,590 --> 00:40:28,425
both chewy and crunchy textures,
it has gotten people addicted

572
00:40:28,426 --> 00:40:30,135
and made it impossible for them to stop.

573
00:40:30,136 --> 00:40:31,386
Leading the witness.

574
00:40:31,387 --> 00:40:34,097
The people ate it of their own free will.

575
00:40:34,098 --> 00:40:37,727
Your Honor, on the charge
of utterly captivating people's minds

576
00:40:38,937 --> 00:40:41,230
I indict the defendant,
pine mushroom japchae.

577
00:40:42,690 --> 00:40:45,443
THE DEFENDANT

578
00:40:50,073 --> 00:40:53,116
THE JUDGE

579
00:40:53,117 --> 00:40:54,285
I will now pass sentence.

580
00:40:54,494 --> 00:40:55,787
The defendant, japchae.

581
00:40:56,871 --> 00:40:58,873
The defendant, japchae, is guilty.

582
00:41:01,125 --> 00:41:03,544
Guilty of being too delicious.

583
00:41:07,298 --> 00:41:09,092
Private First Class Kang Seong-jae
is guilty!

584
00:41:10,843 --> 00:41:14,514
- What?
- Oh, no.

585
00:41:14,764 --> 00:41:16,516
This is absolutely excellent.

586
00:41:18,685 --> 00:41:20,644
So the good morale
in the 4th Company lately

587
00:41:20,645 --> 00:41:23,188
- was all thanks to the food.
- That's right.

588
00:41:23,189 --> 00:41:25,524
Gosh, your skills have improved
quite a bit

589
00:41:25,525 --> 00:41:26,984
since that braised boneless pollack.

590
00:41:26,985 --> 00:41:29,444
Thank you, sir. Maybe because
this is the Officers' Mess

591
00:41:29,445 --> 00:41:31,405
it was possible
because of the great ingredients

592
00:41:31,406 --> 00:41:32,990
like the pine mushrooms.

593
00:41:32,991 --> 00:41:34,825
Precious pine mushrooms?

594
00:41:34,826 --> 00:41:36,076
Of course

595
00:41:36,077 --> 00:41:38,912
the aroma of the pine mushrooms
played a big part in the japchae

596
00:41:38,913 --> 00:41:40,706
but the spinach, onions, and carrots

597
00:41:40,707 --> 00:41:43,001
were of much better quality
in the Officers' Mess.

598
00:41:45,962 --> 00:41:48,255
Are you saying
ingredients to the Officers' Mess

599
00:41:48,256 --> 00:41:50,341
and the Mess Hall are different?

600
00:41:51,968 --> 00:41:53,802
Support Section Chief,
what is going on here?

601
00:41:53,803 --> 00:41:55,013
Well...

602
00:41:55,555 --> 00:41:58,182
It seems there was some kind of mistake.

603
00:41:58,933 --> 00:42:01,601
As far as I know, of all the provisions
that come into the Mess Hall

604
00:42:01,602 --> 00:42:03,061
there haven't been any problems
with any of them.

605
00:42:03,062 --> 00:42:04,897
The difference in the food ingredients

606
00:42:05,898 --> 00:42:07,108
is a fact.

607
00:42:09,068 --> 00:42:10,236
Outpost Commander.

608
00:42:10,987 --> 00:42:12,780
Are you sure you know
what you're talking about?

609
00:42:13,114 --> 00:42:15,574
Since we just signed a provisions contract
with a new company

610
00:42:15,575 --> 00:42:16,867
it's possible that

611
00:42:16,868 --> 00:42:19,494
the previous supplier intentionally
delivered poor-quality provisions.

612
00:42:19,495 --> 00:42:21,622
But I was never informed of anything.

613
00:42:21,831 --> 00:42:23,916
Actually, this isn't something
that just started happening...

614
00:42:25,001 --> 00:42:26,251
I'm sorry.

615
00:42:26,252 --> 00:42:29,337
We should investigate this further
and then report back.

616
00:42:29,338 --> 00:42:30,423
I apologize.

617
00:42:33,342 --> 00:42:35,511
Let's not mess around
when it comes to food.

618
00:42:35,887 --> 00:42:37,262
Battalion Commander,
investigate this thoroughly

619
00:42:37,263 --> 00:42:41,059
- and report back to me. Understood?
- Yes, sir.

620
00:43:00,787 --> 00:43:01,871
Hero.

621
00:43:02,246 --> 00:43:05,750
You have completed the Five-Star Quest.

622
00:43:06,709 --> 00:43:10,588
As a reward, you have acquired
dessert and other cooking recipes.

623
00:43:20,556 --> 00:43:21,640
Thank you.

624
00:43:21,641 --> 00:43:23,810
Thanks to you, I was able to finish
the dish I wanted to make.

625
00:43:25,812 --> 00:43:27,897
It doesn't seem like
you've formally studied cooking.

626
00:43:29,232 --> 00:43:31,109
I first started cooking
after I joined the army.

627
00:43:31,776 --> 00:43:36,155
Anyone could tell.
You looked a bit clumsy and awkward.

628
00:43:37,782 --> 00:43:40,076
I thought I'd improved a lot
since I started

629
00:43:40,785 --> 00:43:42,577
but after coming to the Officers' Mess

630
00:43:42,578 --> 00:43:44,956
I truly feel like I was a frog in a well.

631
00:43:45,331 --> 00:43:48,417
There are so many amazing cooks here.

632
00:43:50,128 --> 00:43:52,380
I didn't expect you
to suddenly serve japchae.

633
00:43:53,005 --> 00:43:55,883
In a way, I guess you could call it bold.

634
00:43:56,467 --> 00:43:58,427
- Thank you.
- That wasn't a compliment.

635
00:43:59,220 --> 00:44:02,306
Even so, I've really learned a lot today.

636
00:44:05,768 --> 00:44:07,603
Could you bring me some of the japchae
you made earlier?

637
00:44:13,860 --> 00:44:16,154
Doesn't he usually avoid eating
food made by others?

638
00:44:16,320 --> 00:44:19,323
He does. He hates ruining his palate.

639
00:44:32,336 --> 00:44:33,504
What do you think?

640
00:44:49,604 --> 00:44:51,272
You seemed so unsure of yourself,
so I was worried.

641
00:44:53,191 --> 00:44:54,317
But it's better than I expected.

642
00:44:57,278 --> 00:44:58,362
Thank you.

643
00:44:59,572 --> 00:45:00,740
Well, but...

644
00:45:01,282 --> 00:45:03,534
If it's not too much to ask

645
00:45:03,743 --> 00:45:07,705
may I also try the dish you made?

646
00:45:16,464 --> 00:45:18,507
- Try it.
- Thank you.

647
00:45:19,258 --> 00:45:23,012
I don't think I've ever had a dish
that looks like this.

648
00:45:25,473 --> 00:45:27,475
It's a French dish called duck confit.

649
00:46:12,478 --> 00:46:14,272
France, the land of gourmet food.

650
00:46:17,316 --> 00:46:18,817
The moment I take a bite

651
00:46:18,818 --> 00:46:23,572
I feel like I'm in the place
that every chef dreams of.

652
00:46:25,783 --> 00:46:26,993
My mouth is filled.

653
00:46:27,410 --> 00:46:31,414
"This is French cuisine!"
It feels like it's shouting that.

654
00:46:44,010 --> 00:46:47,887
Duck confit, six stars.

655
00:46:47,888 --> 00:46:50,433
DUCK CONFIT
IT'S ENTRANCING AND BEAUTIFUL...

656
00:47:04,530 --> 00:47:07,742
It's so delicious. It's absolutely divine.

657
00:47:16,917 --> 00:47:18,752
Why are you being so nice to that guy?

658
00:47:18,753 --> 00:47:20,670
Don't you guys learn anything
from watching him?

659
00:47:20,671 --> 00:47:22,714
We can make japchae with our eyes closed.

660
00:47:22,715 --> 00:47:25,885
You guys, who cook complacently, thinking
"This is good enough"?

661
00:47:43,110 --> 00:47:44,195
I'm sorry.

662
00:47:44,612 --> 00:47:46,572
The Outpost Commander brought up something
she didn't have to.

663
00:47:47,198 --> 00:47:48,240
Seok-ho.

664
00:47:50,326 --> 00:47:53,412
- Yes, Battalion Commander.
- It's not confirmed yet

665
00:47:54,038 --> 00:47:56,456
but when I get promoted
and transferred to headquarters

666
00:47:56,457 --> 00:47:58,250
I'm thinking of having you by my side.

667
00:48:02,129 --> 00:48:03,463
Are you serious, sir?

668
00:48:03,464 --> 00:48:06,634
It's more important for me
to work with people I can trust.

669
00:48:08,386 --> 00:48:09,470
I see.

670
00:48:10,679 --> 00:48:14,766
I had no idea you thought
so highly of me, Battalion Commander.

671
00:48:14,767 --> 00:48:16,560
Well, you always seem so disappointed.

672
00:48:16,936 --> 00:48:19,855
Anyway, I'm planning on taking you
with me, all right?

673
00:48:21,357 --> 00:48:25,403
Yes, sir. I understand completely.

674
00:48:25,861 --> 00:48:26,862
Good.

675
00:48:37,248 --> 00:48:39,041
You should start looking out
for yourself now, shouldn't you?

676
00:48:39,875 --> 00:48:43,211
From now on, I'll take good care of you
so you won't feel left out.

677
00:48:43,212 --> 00:48:44,255
Don't worry.

678
00:48:46,799 --> 00:48:49,260
70TH ANNIVERSARY OF THE ARMY FOUNDING

679
00:48:51,846 --> 00:48:53,264
IM SEUNG-BIN

680
00:49:09,989 --> 00:49:13,033
I thought I had received a skill
that was too good for me

681
00:49:14,368 --> 00:49:17,455
but there are so many people
far more talented than me.

682
00:49:18,664 --> 00:49:20,415
And I've become curious
about the path ahead of me

683
00:49:20,416 --> 00:49:23,335
and just how endlessly it stretches on.

684
00:49:24,837 --> 00:49:26,046
How can I...

685
00:49:26,881 --> 00:49:29,091
learn even more?

686
00:49:33,304 --> 00:49:34,388
I apologize.

687
00:49:36,515 --> 00:49:39,185
You shouldn't have done something
you'd need to apologize for.

688
00:49:39,518 --> 00:49:40,561
Right?

689
00:49:41,479 --> 00:49:42,480
Yes, sir.

690
00:49:43,939 --> 00:49:46,442
They told you to do
a thorough comprehensive inspection

691
00:49:47,526 --> 00:49:50,446
- so do it right.
- I will handle it properly.

692
00:49:51,030 --> 00:49:52,031
Min-gu.

693
00:49:53,532 --> 00:49:55,701
You get what I'm saying, right?

694
00:49:58,913 --> 00:49:59,997
Yes.

695
00:50:01,415 --> 00:50:02,666
Starting with Ganglim Outpost

696
00:50:03,667 --> 00:50:04,752
I will proceed.

697
00:50:04,960 --> 00:50:06,962
BATTALION COMMANDER'S OFFICE

698
00:50:18,974 --> 00:50:22,561
60TH REGIMENT, 1ST BATTALION
GANGLIM

699
00:50:22,686 --> 00:50:23,770
Before roll call next Tuesday

700
00:50:23,771 --> 00:50:25,730
you are scheduled to watch
an educational program

701
00:50:25,731 --> 00:50:26,857
on soldiers' human rights.

702
00:50:27,566 --> 00:50:30,444
- Sir, Company Commander.
- What is it? We're in a meeting.

703
00:50:32,196 --> 00:50:33,197
Well...

704
00:50:34,198 --> 00:50:36,325
I think you need to go
to the mess hall right now.

705
00:50:37,785 --> 00:50:38,910
Here you go.

706
00:50:38,911 --> 00:50:40,996
- Let's hurry up and get some rest.
- Yes, sir.

707
00:50:44,917 --> 00:50:46,752
All right, freeze!

708
00:50:46,877 --> 00:50:48,170
INSPECTION

709
00:50:48,879 --> 00:50:50,339
What? Salute!

710
00:50:50,881 --> 00:50:52,507
As of this moment

711
00:50:52,508 --> 00:50:55,594
I'm conducting a comprehensive inspection
of Ganglim Outpost.

712
00:50:57,638 --> 00:51:00,140
Nice to see you.
Private First Class Kang Seong-jae.

713
00:51:01,183 --> 00:51:02,268
We keep running into each other, don't we?

714
00:51:38,971 --> 00:51:41,432
THE LEGEND OF KITCHEN SOLDIER

715
00:51:41,890 --> 00:51:43,474
We will now conduct
an inspection of all personnel

716
00:51:43,475 --> 00:51:45,185
at Ganglim Outpost.

717
00:51:45,477 --> 00:51:47,228
You are here to be investigated.

718
00:51:47,229 --> 00:51:49,230
Then stop trying to railroad us

719
00:51:49,231 --> 00:51:50,815
and please conduct a proper investigation.

720
00:51:50,816 --> 00:51:54,777
What if I go and ask
the Regimental Commander myself?

721
00:51:54,778 --> 00:51:55,904
Are you confident?

722
00:51:56,155 --> 00:51:58,489
Hey, this has to be the church
the Regimental Commander

723
00:51:58,490 --> 00:52:01,452
- comes to every Sunday, right?
- I made this to give to your daughter.

724
00:52:01,994 --> 00:52:03,495
Are you here, So-yul?

725
00:52:03,954 --> 00:52:05,622
If we give up now,
the Outpost Commander will...

726
00:52:05,623 --> 00:52:07,541
How can you do this so suddenly?

727
00:52:07,750 --> 00:52:10,210
I'm thinking this might be
a good chance to clean up Ganglim.
